********

President Macron, Welcome to Israel!

Today I met with the President of France, H.E. Mr. Emmanuel Macron, together with Blue and White leader, MK Yair Lapid.
We spoke about the recent troubling rise in anti-Semitism in Europe and I thanked him for his determined leadership in fighting this concerning trend in France.
Anti-Semitism is a threat not only to the local Jewish communities of Europe but to the democratic fabric of European society as well.
I also expressed my appreciation for the recent decision by the E3 to activate the Dispute Mechanism of the JCPOA as a means to step up the pressure on Iran. The President and I discussed the strong relationship between the two countries and reflected in the deep collaboration across numerous fronts, which I intend to develop further

Tonight, I met with the AIPAC Board of Directors.
I reiterated the importance of imposing new and increased sanctions on Iran and commended President Trump for his determined actions to prevent it from moving forward on its nuclear project.  
I vowed that as prime minister, I will make certain that all of the Jews in the world feel that Israel is their home, be they Reform, Conservative, or Orthodox. 
At the end of our meeting, I thanked them for their unwavering commitment to the State of Israel and to Israelâ€™s security. The United States is and remains Israelâ€™s closest friend and strategic ally.
